.
Cabin by @jacobwitzling and me 🤗
.

.

node.text: SWIPE 🤗 With pretty much all the work on our Castle Cabin complete, we have been able to get out more and experience our favorite pastime; hiking! Central Oregon is one of the places we love to visit the most and being atop Mt. Tumalo, on the traditional land of The Confederated Tribes of Warm Springs, with epic views of the Cascades, was stunning. However, I couldn’t help but feel anxious about how dry everything was this early in the season. We are killing the planet. The report released today by the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change shows irrefutably that global warming and therefore climate change, is stimulated by humans and that even with drastic measures taken, we’re pretty much f*cked. That is not a call to for us to give up, but for us to get our sh*t together and take this thing seriously. We need to demand that the governments and corporations (coal, oil, gas, etc) that are facilitating the destruction of the planet, change. The individual choices we make are important and I have seriously been reevaluating some of mine. These can be the catalyst but if the companies and regulations do not get drastically altered then we have little to no hope
